    "body": "\r\n> ```\r\n> Set-Item WSMan:\\localhost\\Client\\TrustedHosts -Value $RemoteMachine -force\r\n> $RemoteUsername = 'user'\r\n> $RemotePassword = ' '\r\n> $pass = ConvertTo-SecureString -AsPlainText $RemotePassword -Force\r\n> $Cred = New-Object System.Management.Automation.PSCredential -ArgumentList $RemoteUsername,$pass\r\n> \r\n> Invoke-Command -ComputerName $RemoteMachine -Credential $Cred -ScriptBlock { \r\n>                    & {\r\n>                    diskpart /s c:\\diskman.txt\r\n>                    } } \r\n> ```\r\nIf I remove that `Set-Item` command, I get this error\r\n```\r\nLine |\r\n  75 |  Invoke-Command -ComputerName $RemoteMachine -Credential $Cred -Script …\r\n     |  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n     | This parameter set requires WSMan, and no supported WSMan client library was found. WSMan\r\n     | is either not installed or unavailable for this system.\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
