    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I also installed PSWSMan and WSManTrust modules as I thought those will fix the problem (based on the descriptions).\r\n```\r\nPS /home/mahmood> Get-InstalledModule\r\n\r\nVersion              Name                                Repository           Description\r\n-------              ----                                ----------           -----------\r\n1.0.0                Microsoft.PowerShell.SecretStore    PSGallery            This PowerShell module is an extension vault for the Po…\r\n2.2.0                PSWSMan                             PSGallery            Module to install and manage the forked WSMan client li…\r\n0.1.45.0             WSManTrust                          PSGallery            Cmdlets to manage WSMan trust settings.\r\n1.0.0                Microsoft.PowerShell.SecretManagem… PSGallery            This module provides a convenient way for a user to sto…\r\n\r\nPS /home/mahmood> Set-Item WSMan:\\localhost\\Client\\TrustedHosts -Value $RemoteMachine -force\r\nSet-Item: Cannot find drive. A drive with the name 'WSMan' does not exist.\r\nPS /home/mahmood> $RemoteUsername = 'user'\r\nPS /home/mahmood> $RemotePassword = ' '\r\nPS /home/mahmood> $pass = ConvertTo-SecureString -AsPlainText $RemotePassword -Force\r\nPS /home/mahmood> $Cred = New-Object System.Management.Automation.PSCredential -ArgumentList $RemoteUsername,$pass\r\nPS /home/mahmood> $RemoteMachine = \"10.1.1.51\"\r\nPS /home/mahmood> Set-Item WSMan:\\localhost\\Client\\TrustedHosts -Value $RemoteMachine -force\r\nSet-Item: Cannot find drive. A drive with the name 'WSMan' does not exist.\r\nPS /home/mahmood> Invoke-Command -ComputerName $RemoteMachine -Credential $Cred -ScriptBlock {diskpart /s c:\\diskman.txt}\r\nInvoke-Command: This parameter set requires WSMan, and no supported WSMan client library was found. WSMan is either not installed or unavailable for this system.\r\n```",
